    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-19T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-19T20:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.24 <gloss target="#t_FLC1">FLC</gloss>/5–1947:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-19T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 19, 1947—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>388. My telegram 387, May 19.<note n="39" xml:id="d477fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    Chilean Air Force also informs me that they desire utilize balance between one
                    million dollars authorized and expenditures covering delivery air equipment
                    already in <pb facs="0540" n="524" xml:id="pg_524"/> Chile to purchase eight
                    Beechcraft <gloss target="#t_AT111">AT–11</gloss>’s and 556,000 rounds 50
                    caliber ammunition which they state would cover one year’s training. Shipping
                    expenses will be for account of Chilean Government.</p>
                <p>Air Attaché<note n="40" xml:id="d477fn2">Lt. Col. Robert Lewis Coffey, Jr.</note>
                    urgently recommending to his superiors that Beech-crafts and ammunition be
                    supplied to Chile. I strongly concur.<note n="41" xml:id="d477fn3">In telegram
                        483, September 29, 1947, to Santiago, the Department indicated the
                        consummation of a contract for the <gloss target="#t_AT111">AT–11</gloss>
                        planes (825.24 <gloss target="#t_FLC1">FLC</gloss>/9–2947).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
